    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:ComicStory</AbbreviatedIRI>
        <Literal>The term &quot;story&quot; is any indivisible, re-printable
        unit of a comic, including the interior stories, covers, and backmatter. Most
        comics have at least two stories: a cover (ComicCoverArt) and an interior story.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:ComicStory</AbbreviatedIRI>
        <Literal>ComicStory</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:Comment</AbbreviatedIRI>
        <Literal>A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment&apos;s content is expressed via the &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/text&quot;&gt;text&lt;/a&gt; property, and its topic via &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/about&quot;&gt;about&lt;/a&gt;, properties shared with all CreativeWorks.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:Comment</AbbreviatedIRI>
        <Literal>Comment</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
