    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:WebContent</AbbreviatedIRI>
        <Literal>WebContent is a type representing all &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebPage&quot;&gt;WebPage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebSite&quot;&gt;WebSite&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebPageElement&quot;&gt;WebPageElement&lt;/a&gt; content. It is sometimes the case that detailed distinctions between Web pages, sites and their parts is not always important or obvious. The  &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebContent&quot;&gt;WebContent&lt;/a&gt; type makes it easier to describe Web-addressable content without requiring such distinctions to always be stated. (The intent is that the existing types &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebPage&quot;&gt;WebPage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebSite&quot;&gt;WebSite&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebPageElement&quot;&gt;WebPageElement&lt;/a&gt; will eventually be declared as subtypes of &lt;a class=&quot;localLink&quot; href=&quot;http://schema.org/WebContent&quot;&gt;WebContent&lt;/a&gt;.)</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <AbbreviatedIRI>schema1:WebContent</AbbreviatedIRI>
